@@ -0,0 +1,107 @@
+# Runbook: Feature Schema Compare (P104)
+
+## Purpose
+
+Nightly job compares two ML feature schemas (default `v5_of` vs `v6_of`) on the **same** recent data window:
+
+- builds one dataset from Redis (`signals:of:inputs` + `trades:closed`),
+- runs `feature_selection_loop_v1` twice (per schema),
+- publishes a low-cardinality summary to Redis hash `metrics:feature_schema_compare:last`,
+- exporter exposes Prometheus metrics used by alerts and the Grafana dashboard.
+
+The goal is to catch regressions early and provide a quick view of:
+
+- **delta_auc = AUC(schema_b) - AUC(schema_a)** (positive is good),
+- **delta_brier = Brier(schema_b) - Brier(schema_a)** (negative is good),
+- **noise_share** stability proxy (share of "noisy" features by regime/hour).
+
+## Alerts
+
+- `FeatureSchemaCompareFailed`: last run failed.
+- `FeatureSchemaCompareStale`: no update for > 6h.
+- `FeatureSchemaCompareExporterDown`: exporter cannot expose metrics.
+- `FeatureSchemaCompareQualityRegression`: `delta_auc < -0.010`.
+- `FeatureSchemaCompareCalibrationRegression`: `delta_brier > 0.0005`.
+
+## Quick checks
+
+### 1) Check Prometheus / Grafana
+
+Open dashboard: **Feature Schema Compare (P104)**
+
+- Last success
+- Age seconds
+- delta_auc / delta_brier
+- AUC/Brier and noise_share by schema
+
+### 2) Check Redis summary (source of truth)
+
+```bash
+redis-cli HGETALL metrics:feature_schema_compare:last
+```
+
+Key fields:
+
+- `status`, `reason`, `success`, `run_id`
+- `schema_a`, `schema_b`
+- `auc_a`, `auc_b`, `brier_a`, `brier_b`
+- `delta_auc`, `delta_brier`
+- `noise_share_a`, `noise_share_b`
+- `report_path` (compare report in filesystem)
+
+### 3) Inspect the compare report
+
+On the host where the job runs:
+
+```bash
+cat "$(redis-cli HGET metrics:feature_schema_compare:last report_path)"
+```
+
+It contains:
+
+- quality table
+- top new features in schema_b (by perm AUC drop)
+- links to per-schema reports
+
+## Remediation
+
+### If `FeatureSchemaCompareFailed`
+
+1) Verify the job ran (systemd timer / docker-compose timers / cron).
+2) Inspect logs of the runner container/service.
+3) Validate connectivity:
+
+- Redis URL / credentials (`REDIS_URL`)
+- stream names exist (`signals:of:inputs`, `trades:closed`)
+
+4) Re-run manually:
+
+```bash
+python -m ml_analysis.tools.nightly_feature_schema_compare_bundle_v1 \
+  --schema_a v5_of --schema_b v6_of \
+  --window_hours 168
+```
+
+### If `delta_auc` regression / `delta_brier` regression
+
+1) **Do not promote** schema_b.
+2) Review **top new features** (compare report) and remove/denylist the worst offenders.
+3) Increase robustness:
+
+- raise `FEATURE_SCHEMA_COMPARE_MIN_GROUP_ROWS`
+- increase `FEATURE_SCHEMA_COMPARE_WINDOW_HOURS`
+- consider `model=gbdt` for a nonlinear check (still quick)
+
+4) Re-run compare after changes.
+
+## Config (env)
+
+- `FEATURE_SCHEMA_COMPARE_SCHEMA_A` (default `v5_of`)
